  "title": "PM / Business Analyst – KYC & AML",
  "description": "<p>PM cum Business Analyst to support a large-scale KYC/AML programme for an international bank. The role supports multiple implementation phases and works closely with the Project Manager and PMO on delivery governance, reporting, and coordination.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Support PMO activities including plan tracking, RAID management, status reporting, and dashboards</li><li>Track milestones, dependencies, and delivery across multiple workstreams</li><li>Coordinate with Business, IT, Operations, Compliance, and vendors</li><li>Gather, document, and manage business and functional requirements</li><li>Prepare BA artefacts (BRD/FRD, user stories, data mapping)</li><li>Own UAT activities: scope definition, test scenarios, execution support, and defect closure</li><li>Apply KYC/AML knowledge (CDD, EDD, risk assessment, regulatory expectations) to requirements and testing</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>5+ years’ experience in BA, PMO, or delivery roles within banking</li><li>Strong hands-on experience in KYC/AML programmes</li><li>Experience working on regulatory or IT transformation projects</li><li>Strong communication, documentation, and stakeholder management skills</li><li>Hands-on with Jira, Confluence, Excel, PowerPoint, MS Project (or similar tools)</li></ul><p><strong>Good to Have</strong></p><ul><li>Experience with  global banks</li><li>Exposure to large programme PMO, audit, or change management</li></ul>",
